shatner, also known as capt. james t. kirk of ``star trek'' fame, spent half an hour with the celebrated 16-year-old lowland gorilla at the gorilla foundation saturday. koko lives at the nonprofit organization's center and has been taught to understand 2,000 words of spoken english and use a vocabulary of 600 signs
koko and i talked,'' shatner said. ``we touched hands and we touched minds. feeling her powerful hand on the back of my neck was unlike any other experience i've known.''
